has been clearly recorded on tape.

354
00:25:08,273 --> 00:25:09,475
That's not possible!

355
00:25:10,175 --> 00:25:12,711
Even though my husband didn't have
much progress throughout his life,

356
00:25:12,778 --> 00:25:16,181
he would never do anything
that would bring shame to our family.

357
00:25:16,648 --> 00:25:18,317
Especially anything illegal.

358
00:25:18,384 --> 00:25:20,586
He just doesn't have the guts!

359
00:25:20,953 --> 00:25:23,088
You must've made a mistake, sir.

360
00:25:23,455 --> 00:25:26,025
You can't wrong an innocent person
like this.

361
00:25:26,091 --> 00:25:27,693
You can't do this!

362
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:30,095
My husband would never
do something like that!

363
00:25:30,162 --> 00:25:31,363
Anyway, Mrs. Dong,

364
00:25:31,730 --> 00:25:35,968
please tell your husband to return
the company car as soon as possible.

365
00:25:36,402 --> 00:25:38,137
Or else, the company will call the police.

366
00:25:39,004 --> 00:25:40,939
That's it. Goodbye.

367
00:25:41,774 --> 00:25:42,941
Call the police?

368
00:25:43,776 --> 00:25:45,677
Sir!

369
00:25:46,145 --> 00:25:49,748
My husband would never do
that kind of thing!

370
00:25:58,390 --> 00:25:59,224
Hello?

371
00:26:00,125 --> 00:26:02,594
Honey, where are you now?

372
00:26:04,897 --> 00:26:06,899
Meet you at the Warner Village?

373
00:26:09,168 --> 00:26:11,670
Honey, there's something
I need to ask you.

374
00:26:12,438 --> 00:26:13,305
Honey!

375
00:26:13,972 --> 00:26:14,973
Honey...

376
00:26:16,275 --> 00:26:17,743
What's going on?

377
00:26:18,210 --> 00:26:22,548
WARNER VILLAGE

378
00:26:28,187 --> 00:26:29,254
Strange.

379
00:26:53,545 --> 00:26:54,379
Honey!

380
00:26:55,247 --> 00:26:56,081
Honey!

381
00:26:58,117 --> 00:26:59,118
It's me.

382
00:26:59,351 --> 00:27:00,552
Get in the car!

383
00:27:01,553 --> 00:27:03,155
I can't park here.

384
00:27:03,755 --> 00:27:04,923
Hurry up!

385
00:27:07,993 --> 00:27:09,561
Get in the car, hurry.

386
00:27:10,929 --> 00:27:11,997
Hurry up!

387
00:27:13,098 --> 00:27:14,099
Come, get in.

388
00:27:15,534 --> 00:27:17,936
Look, isn't this a cool car?

389
00:27:18,237 --> 00:27:19,338
How hot is it?

390
00:27:19,404 --> 00:27:21,140
Buckle up.

391
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:22,441
Here we go!

392
00:27:25,043 --> 00:27:26,078
I'll take you on a trip.

393
00:27:31,984 --> 00:27:32,985
Wow.

394
00:27:33,619 --> 00:27:35,154
A good car is a good car.

395
00:27:35,954 --> 00:27:37,823
It's very smooth, isn't it?

396
00:27:39,424 --> 00:27:41,560
When you sit in a luxury car like this,

397
00:27:43,061 --> 00:27:44,596
you feel superior.

398
00:27:44,663 --> 00:27:45,964
Don't you think so, honey?

399
00:27:48,233 --> 00:27:50,802
Comfortable? Feels good, right?

400
00:27:56,842 --> 00:27:58,610
-Honey.
-Yes?

401
00:27:59,945 --> 00:28:01,947
Where did you get this car?

402
00:28:07,586 --> 00:28:08,654
Honey.

403
00:28:10,556 --> 00:28:14,326
I remember when I proposed to you,

404
00:28:15,294 --> 00:28:16,461
I told you

405
00:28:17,596 --> 00:28:20,199
that I'd make you a glamorous Mrs. Dong.

406
00:28:22,167 --> 00:28:23,669
But after marrying me,

407
00:28:24,536 --> 00:28:26,772
I only let you bear hardships with me.

408
00:28:27,239 --> 00:28:29,474
You've never known
what a good life is like.

409
00:28:31,443 --> 00:28:33,011
Not to mention being glamorous.

410
00:28:34,746 --> 00:28:36,081
So, tonight,

411
00:28:37,716 --> 00:28:40,619
I must let you enjoy
the most luxurious car.

412
00:28:41,787 --> 00:28:45,958
Let me drive you around
and take you for a joyride.

413
00:28:49,728 --> 00:28:50,929
I've been thinking.

414
00:28:53,298 --> 00:28:55,100
Even though I'm incompetent,

415
00:28:56,101 --> 00:28:58,971
at least I'll make you
feel glamorous for today.

416
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:02,574
It's been so many years.

417
00:29:04,676 --> 00:29:06,845
Today, my wish has finally been granted.

418
00:29:10,582 --> 00:29:14,086
Honey, happy birthday.

419
00:29:39,278 --> 00:29:40,345
Honey,

420
00:29:42,447 --> 00:29:43,582
thank you.

421
00:30:00,766 --> 00:30:01,700
Honey,

422
00:30:03,001 --> 00:30:04,469
are you happy today?

423
00:30:06,305 --> 00:30:07,306
Yes.

424
00:30:13,979 --> 00:30:16,315
I feel so happy today.

425
00:30:24,122 --> 00:30:25,023
Honey,

426
00:30:25,791 --> 00:30:29,861
I actually never cared

427
00:30:30,262 --> 00:30:32,364
about what kind of life we live.

428
00:30:32,998 --> 00:30:35,233
It also never mattered to me

429
00:30:35,300 --> 00:30:37,703
whether you've let us live
a good life or not.

430
00:30:38,570 --> 00:30:40,906
Because I know you work very hard.

431
00:30:41,773 --> 00:30:42,908
Therefore,

432
00:30:43,308 --> 00:30:46,411
every day with you

433
00:30:47,279 --> 00:30:51,149
is a happy day for me.

434
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:56,521
Honey.

435
00:30:59,224 --> 00:31:04,396
I hope you'll always be this happy.

436
00:31:59,217 --> 00:32:01,720
Honey, let's park the car here.

437
00:32:01,820 --> 00:32:03,388
The alley to our house is so narrow.

438
00:32:03,455 --> 00:32:07,225
If we are not careful, we might damage
the car. How will we compensate for that?

439
00:32:07,292 --> 00:32:08,126
Right.

440
00:32:08,193 --> 00:32:10,195
Return the car soon.

441
00:32:10,262 --> 00:32:11,129
-I will.
-Honey.

442
00:32:11,196 --> 00:32:13,098
I'm going to return it.

443
00:32:13,465 --> 00:32:14,866
I'm just driving you home first.

444
00:32:15,434 --> 00:32:18,737
So that we can have
a perfect ending for tonight,

445
00:32:19,304 --> 00:32:21,406
and also bring you the best memories.

446
00:32:21,606 --> 00:32:22,441
Yeah?

447
00:32:22,507 --> 00:32:23,575
Thank you, honey.

448
00:32:26,378 --> 00:32:27,646
Honey, wait.

449
00:32:29,014 --> 00:32:30,115
Wait a moment.

450
00:32:36,621 --> 00:32:39,024
Honey, go ahead.

451
00:32:44,663 --> 00:32:45,797
Is this the car?

452
00:32:47,766 --> 00:32:48,733
Sir.

453
00:32:49,234 --> 00:32:52,103
Sir, let me explain.

454
00:32:52,170 --> 00:32:55,106
-I wanted to boost the car sales.
-Yes.

455
00:32:55,173 --> 00:32:58,310
So I drove the car out today
to test its performance.

456
00:32:58,410 --> 00:33:01,413
I have now understood
and studied its every feature.

457
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:03,782
I am about to drive it back
to the company.

458
00:33:03,849 --> 00:33:04,983
Yes.

459
00:33:05,050 --> 00:33:06,251
-The car key.
-What?

460
00:33:11,857 --> 00:33:14,059
-Please come with us.
-Come with you?

461
00:33:14,125 --> 00:33:15,861
You want to test drive?
Sure, I'll take you there.

462
00:33:15,927 --> 00:33:17,596
-This car's got great performance.
-Yes, great.

463
00:33:17,662 --> 00:33:19,664
Stop playing innocent.
Come with us to the police station.

464
00:33:19,731 --> 00:33:20,732
Come.

465
00:33:21,132 --> 00:33:23,768
Is it that serious?
It's not necessary, is it, sir?

466
00:33:23,835 --> 00:33:26,438
Sir, please forgive my husband.

467
00:33:26,505 --> 00:33:28,573
This is his first time stealing a car.

468
00:33:29,741 --> 00:33:32,110
Don't talk nonsense! Who's stealing?

469
00:33:32,177 --> 00:33:33,712
Am I the type of person who steals a car?

470
00:33:33,778 --> 00:33:35,580
I was only borrowing it.

471
00:33:35,647 --> 00:33:38,216
Yes. This is the first time
he has borrowed a car.

472
00:33:38,617 --> 00:33:39,618
Dong.

473
00:33:40,151 --> 00:33:43,088
This car belongs to the company.
Do you just borrow it whenever you wish?

474
00:33:43,522 --> 00:33:45,090
The company doesn't approve
of your behavior.

475
00:33:45,156 --> 00:33:46,625
I'm also jointly liable.

476
00:33:47,826 --> 00:33:49,928
Officers, excuse me.

477
00:33:50,762 --> 00:33:53,064
-No. Don't.
-Let's go.

478
00:33:53,498 --> 00:33:55,400
Officers, you've got it wrong.

479
00:33:55,467 --> 00:33:56,635
Ma'am, please do not interfere.

480
00:33:56,701 --> 00:33:58,503
-You've got it wrong.
-We have a lot of work to do.

481
00:33:58,570 --> 00:33:59,404
Seriously, please?

482
00:33:59,471 --> 00:34:02,507
-This is a mistake. Let him go!
-You're interfering with public duty.

483
00:34:02,574 --> 00:34:04,576
What are you guys doing?
What's going on, Mom?

484
00:34:04,643 --> 00:34:07,045
-Shancai.
-Mr. Dong...

485
00:34:08,780 --> 00:34:11,650
Wait a minute. What did my father do?
Why are you taking him?

486
00:34:11,716 --> 00:34:15,353
Shancai, tell them that your dad
would never steal a car.

487
00:34:15,420 --> 00:34:16,721
-He would never...
-Steal a car?

488
00:34:16,788 --> 00:34:18,723
Shancai, believe me.

489
00:34:18,790 --> 00:34:21,326
I didn't steal it.
I was just borrowing it.

490
00:34:22,627 --> 00:34:24,896
You said my father stole the car.
Do you have any evidence?

491
00:34:24,963 --> 00:34:27,599
Miss, your father stole a company car.

492
00:34:27,933 --> 00:34:29,467
Now he's here with the car.

493
00:34:30,635 --> 00:34:32,704
That's impossible.
There must be some misunderstanding.

494
00:34:33,204 --> 00:34:34,272
Excuse me.

495
00:34:35,340 --> 00:34:36,308
Lei.

496
00:34:37,742 --> 00:34:38,743
Mr. Dong,

497
00:34:39,744 --> 00:34:41,613
is this the car I ordered from you?

498
00:34:42,581 --> 00:34:44,416
Lei, when did you...

499
00:34:45,216 --> 00:34:46,351
Master Huaze.

500
00:34:46,818 --> 00:34:48,353
You said this was the car you ordered?

501
00:34:48,420 --> 00:34:49,287
Yeah.

502
00:34:51,022 --> 00:34:52,357
Dong, what the hell?

503
00:34:52,591 --> 00:34:55,026
I... Yes.

504
00:34:56,695 --> 00:34:58,530
Because I urgently need the car tonight,

505
00:34:59,064 --> 00:35:01,433
I asked Mr. Dong to drive it here for me.

506
00:35:03,234 --> 00:35:05,103
Honey...

507
00:35:09,407 --> 00:35:11,710
I was supposed to pick up the car here.
Wasn't I, Mr. Dong?

508
00:35:12,210 --> 00:35:14,279
Yes.

509
00:35:18,617 --> 00:35:19,451
Lei.

510
00:35:23,521 --> 00:35:26,057
Lei, thank you.

511
00:35:31,863 --> 00:35:33,531
Do we need to be so polite to each other?

512
00:35:59,691 --> 00:36:02,527
Why do you always show up
when I'm most vulnerable?

513
00:36:11,469 --> 00:36:12,504
Shancai.

514
00:36:14,572 --> 00:36:15,940
Have you ever thought about it?

515
00:36:19,310 --> 00:36:21,680
If Ah Si never regains his memory,

516
00:36:25,650 --> 00:36:27,585
what change will it make to the world?

517
00:36:40,365 --> 00:36:41,800
The Earth will still be turning.

518
00:36:44,302 --> 00:36:45,904
The sun will still rise every day.

519
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:52,143
The stars will still be out
in the night sky.

520
00:36:54,846 --> 00:36:56,481
You will still work hard to live.

521
00:36:58,817 --> 00:37:00,785
I will still sleep for 12 hours a day.

522
00:37:02,921 --> 00:37:04,355
Nothing will change.

523
00:37:08,860 --> 00:37:09,861
Yeah.

524
00:37:10,395 --> 00:37:11,896
Nothing will change.

525
00:37:13,698 --> 00:37:15,166
The only thing that changed...

526
00:37:16,468 --> 00:37:18,203
was Daoming Si left me.

527
00:37:23,241 --> 00:37:24,309
Don't worry about it.

528
00:37:25,910 --> 00:37:27,345
Ah Si has lost his memory for now.

529
00:37:29,214 --> 00:37:31,549
Who knows if he will
remember everything someday?

530
00:37:50,735 --> 00:37:51,736
Shancai.

531
00:37:53,338 --> 00:37:56,441
A lot of tomorrows are waiting for you
in this world.

532
00:38:01,012 --> 00:38:05,617
Good thing that you're back.

533
00:38:51,830 --> 00:38:54,499
TAKE CARE

534
00:39:14,719 --> 00:39:17,055
<i>Didn't you say that stars
would provide direction?</i>

535
00:39:17,422 --> 00:39:19,057
There are no stars in Taipei.

536
00:39:19,657 --> 00:39:20,758
No stars?

537
00:39:22,126 --> 00:39:23,194
It's true.

538
00:39:23,261 --> 00:39:24,762
I don't see Brave Yesha, too.

539
00:40:32,530 --> 00:40:33,364
Daoming Si.

540
00:40:35,133 --> 00:40:36,067
Where's Yesha?

541
00:40:36,534 --> 00:40:37,535
I have no idea.

542
00:40:37,602 --> 00:40:39,270
I've waited for so long
but I haven't seen her.

543
00:40:40,371 --> 00:40:41,773
Why are you at the airport?

544
00:40:43,708 --> 00:40:45,510
Did she tell you
that she was going to Barcelona?

545
00:40:46,010 --> 00:40:48,246
She said she was going to travel
around the world.

546
00:40:48,846 --> 00:40:49,847
She...

547
00:40:52,350 --> 00:40:53,785
What sort of things did you say to her?

548
00:40:55,787 --> 00:40:57,221
Why did you force her to leave?

549
00:40:58,823 --> 00:41:01,759
How can you be so selfish?

550
00:41:05,263 --> 00:41:09,434
I will never forgive you.

551
00:41:24,015 --> 00:41:25,249
I was just wondering

552
00:41:25,984 --> 00:41:27,719
if I could wake you up by slapping you.

553
00:41:35,560 --> 00:41:36,728
Daoming Si!

554
00:42:03,755 --> 00:42:06,090
DAOMING SI

555
00:42:07,058 --> 00:42:09,060
I'LL BE WAITING FOR YOU

556
00:44:03,608 --> 00:44:05,676
She must be in Barcelona by now.

557
00:44:12,416 --> 00:44:14,352
Maybe she's at a château already.

558
00:44:17,955 --> 00:44:20,024
Unfortunately, you haven't been
to any châteaux there.

559
00:44:25,396 --> 00:44:27,765
Sha's dishes are different
from what you would expect.

560
00:44:32,503 --> 00:44:35,039
And the sunset over there
is different from here, too.

561
00:46:15,773 --> 00:46:17,775
Subtitle translation by I Lin Lee
